# Factor Attribution Model — Build Prompt Pack

Delivery target: Python pipeline → single self-contained interactive HTML dashboard (Plotly).
Run: `python run.py --input monthly_returns.xlsx --config config.yaml --output dashboard.html`

Use these prompts in sequence (Claude Code or similar). Prompt 0 sets context for the whole
session; paste it first and keep the session alive, or prepend it to each prompt if starting fresh.

---

## Prompt 0 — Project context (paste first, always)

```
You are building a return-based factor performance attribution model for a long-only
global equity fund, for internal investment-risk oversight.

Architecture:
- Python 3.11+, libraries: pandas, numpy, statsmodels, scikit-learn, plotly, pyyaml, openpyxl.
- Modular package layout:
    attribution_model/
        data_loader.py      # load + validate monthly returns
        factor_builder.py   # raw index returns -> relative factor returns
        model.py            # staged OLS regression engine
        attribution.py      # monthly + cumulative factor contributions
        risk.py             # tracking-error variance decomposition
        diagnostics.py      # VIF, correlations, rolling betas, residual checks
        dashboard.py        # render single-file interactive HTML (Plotly)
        run.py              # CLI entry point orchestrating the pipeline
        config.yaml         # benchmark, factor list, horizons, tolerances
- Final deliverable: ONE self-contained HTML file (all Plotly JS + data embedded,
  no external CDN dependency, works offline on a locked-down corporate machine).
- Input: one Excel/CSV monthly total-return table:
  Date | Fund | Benchmark | <market index> | <style indices> | <sector indices> | <country indices>
- All returns monthly, end-of-month aligned, total return, same currency.

Modelling rules (fixed, do not deviate):
- Dependent variable: geometric relative return
  y_t = (1 + r_fund,t) / (1 + r_benchmark,t) - 1
- Each factor: relative return vs its parent index, x_i,t = r_factorIndex,t - r_parentIndex,t
- Regression: OLS with Newey-West (HAC) standard errors, monthly data, ~60 observations.
- Staged estimation for interpretability:
  Stage 1 market only -> Stage 2 + style -> Stage 3 + industry -> Stage 4 + country.
  Report incremental R² per stage.
- Max ~10-12 factors; if VIF > 5 or |correlation| > 0.75, flag and support
  ridge/lasso fallback via config.
- Attribution: contribution_i,t = beta_i * x_i,t; residual = actual - fitted;
  alpha reported separately (annualised).
- Horizons: trailing 12m, 36m, 60m. Geometric linking is the default reporting basis
  (arithmetic sum available as secondary); components must reconcile to total
  compounded relative return within a config tolerance (default 1bp).

Code standards: type hints, docstrings, no hard-coded factor names (everything from
config.yaml), raise clear errors on bad data, deterministic output.

Confirm you understand, then wait for module instructions.
```

