## Prompt 1 — config.yaml + data_loader.py

```
Build config.yaml and data_loader.py.

config.yaml must define:
- input file path and sheet name
- column mapping: fund, benchmark, market index
- factor blocks: style, industry, country — each factor with
  {name, index_column, parent_column}
- horizons: [12, 36, 60]
- regression: {se_type: newey_west, nw_lags: 3, regularisation: none|ridge|lasso, ridge_alpha}
- thresholds: {vif_flag: 5, corr_flag: 0.75, reconciliation_tol_bps: 1}
- attribution: {linking: geometric|arithmetic, alpha_treatment: separate|in_residual}

data_loader.py must:
1. Load the Excel/CSV, parse Date to month-end timestamps, sort ascending.
2. Validate: all configured columns present; at least 60 monthly observations
   (warn, don't fail, if 36-59; fail below 36); no duplicate dates; contiguous
   monthly calendar (report any gaps).
3. Data-quality checks with a structured report object:
   - missing values per column (report location)
   - stale prices: 3+ identical consecutive returns in any index (flag)
   - index launch-date limitation: leading NaNs in any factor column (flag,
     record usable start date per factor)
   - extreme values: |monthly return| > 25% (flag for review, don't drop)
4. Return (a) clean DataFrame of decimal returns, (b) DataQualityReport dataclass
   that the dashboard will later render as a data-audit panel.
5. Include a small synthetic-data generator (make_synthetic_returns()) producing
   60 months of plausible correlated returns for all configured columns, so the
   full pipeline can be tested end-to-end without licensed MSCI data.

Write unit tests (pytest) for the validation logic.
```

