## Prompt 2 — factor_builder.py

```
Build factor_builder.py: transform raw index returns into regression-ready
relative factor returns.

Requirements:
1. Dependent variable: Fund_Rel_t = (1 + Fund_t) / (1 + Benchmark_t) - 1.
2. Market factor: MKT_t = r_market_index,t - r_benchmark,t. If config says the
   benchmark IS the market index, omit the market factor entirely (support
   market_factor: null in config).
3. Every style/industry/country factor: x_i,t = r_index,t - r_parent,t using
   the parent defined per-factor in config (parents can differ, e.g. sector
   indices vs MSCI World, country indices vs MSCI World).
4. Output a tidy factor DataFrame: Date | Fund_Rel | MKT | <factor columns>,
   restricted to the intersection of usable dates across all factors.
5. Produce a factor construction audit table (per factor: name, block,
   index column, parent column, first usable date, n obs, mean, ann. vol) —
   this feeds a dashboard audit panel and satisfies the governance requirement
   that every factor is observable and independently sourced.
6. Compute and store the factor correlation matrix; flag any pair with
   |corr| > threshold from config.

Unit tests: correct relative-return arithmetic (hand-computed cases), correct
handling of null market factor, correct date intersection with staggered
launch dates.
```

