## Prompt 3 — model.py (staged regression engine)

```
Build model.py: the staged regression engine.

Requirements:
1. Four cumulative stages on the full sample:
   Stage 1: Fund_Rel ~ const + MKT
   Stage 2: + style block
   Stage 3: + industry block
   Stage 4: + country block (final model)
   (If market factor is null, Stage 1 is intercept-only or skipped; handle both.)
2. Estimation: statsmodels OLS with Newey-West HAC covariance (maxlags from config).
3. For every stage store: betas, HAC t-stats, p-values, R², adjusted R²,
   residual monthly vol (annualise ×√12), and incremental R² vs previous stage.
4. Final-model extras:
   - VIF per factor (flag > config threshold)
   - tracking error explained: 1 - Var(resid)/Var(Fund_Rel), plus annualised
     realised TE and annualised residual vol
   - alpha annualised: (1 + alpha_monthly)^12 - 1
5. Regularisation fallback: if config regularisation = ridge or lasso,
   fit sklearn on standardised factors, back-transform coefficients to the
   original return scale so attribution stays in return space. Document in
   the output object which estimator produced the final betas.
6. Rolling stability: optional rolling 36-month OLS on the final spec;
   store rolling betas per factor; flag any factor whose rolling beta changes
   sign or moves by more than 2 full-sample standard errors.
7. Return a single ModelResult object (dataclass) carrying everything above —
   attribution.py, risk.py and dashboard.py consume only this object.

Unit tests: recover known betas from synthetic data with planted loadings;
VIF computation vs manual calc; ridge back-transform correctness.
```

