## Prompt 6 — diagnostics.py

```
Build diagnostics.py: assemble the governance/diagnostics pack from the
ModelResult and factor data.

Contents (all as tidy DataFrames ready for dashboard rendering):
1. Coefficient table: factor | block | beta | HAC t-stat | p-value |
   significance stars | VIF | flags.
2. Stage R² table: stage | R² | adj R² | incremental R².
3. Factor correlation matrix with cells flagged where |corr| > threshold.
4. Rolling 36m beta series per factor + stability flags (sign change,
   > 2 SE drift).
5. Residual analysis: residual time series, largest 5 unexplained months
   (date, actual, fitted, residual) — each labelled "for qualitative review",
   never auto-labelled as skill.
6. Data-quality report passthrough from data_loader.
7. A one-page governance summary dict: n obs, n factors, parsimony check
   (factors vs 10-12 guideline), estimator used, reconciliation status,
   TE explained, list of all active flags. This becomes the dashboard's
   "Model governance" panel.
```

