## Prompt 7 — dashboard.py (the HTML deliverable)

```
Build dashboard.py: render everything into ONE self-contained interactive
HTML file. This is the primary deliverable.

Technical requirements:
- Plotly with include_plotlyjs='inline' (fully offline, no CDN).
- All tables/figures embedded; file opens in any modern browser from a
  network drive or email attachment.
- Clean internal-report aesthetic: neutral palette, one accent colour,
  clear typography, generous white space. Header with fund name, benchmark,
  data window, run timestamp, config hash (for audit).

Layout (tabbed or anchored sections):
1. HEADLINE — the sentence: "Over five years the fund outperformed its
   benchmark by X%; Y% style, Z% sector, A% country, B% market, C% specific/
   residual" — generated dynamically from results, plus a headline bar chart
   of block contributions with a 1y / 3y / 5y toggle (Plotly updatemenus or
   buttons — no server needed).
2. ATTRIBUTION — main summary table (blocks × horizons) with expandable
   factor-level detail (style, sector, country sub-tables shown/hidden with
   a few lines of vanilla JS); geometric basis default, arithmetic shown
   with reconciliation gap; waterfall chart per horizon.
3. TIME SERIES — cumulative actual vs fitted relative return; monthly
   stacked contribution area chart by block; residual bar chart with the
   5 largest unexplained months annotated.
4. RISK — TE decomposition donut/bar beside the return attribution so
   return-vs-risk contrast is visible; TE explained metric.
5. DIAGNOSTICS — coefficient table with significance and VIF flags
   (conditional cell highlighting), stage R² progression, correlation
   heatmap, rolling beta small-multiples with stability flags.
6. GOVERNANCE & DATA — governance summary panel (all flags in one place),
   factor construction audit table, data-quality report.

Interactivity rules: everything client-side (Plotly toggles + minimal
vanilla JS for expand/collapse). No external requests. Dashboard must
degrade gracefully if optional sections (rolling betas) were not run.

Also build run.py: CLI (argparse) wiring the full pipeline
load -> build factors -> model -> attribution -> risk -> diagnostics -> dashboard,
with --input, --config, --output, --synthetic (uses the synthetic generator
for an end-to-end demo). Print a short console summary and the output path.

Acceptance test: `python run.py --synthetic --output demo.html` produces a
working dashboard with every section populated.
```

